WEBVTT

00:02.380 --> 00:03.380
Kevin: My life
was going pretty terrible.

00:03.380 --> 00:04.790
I lost my job,

00:04.790 --> 00:06.040
had to move in with my sister
and my niece.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.420
You think you can just
come into our lives?

00:07.420 --> 00:08.750
I don't even know you.

00:08.750 --> 00:10.080
I'm here now.

00:10.080 --> 00:12.080
And then, things got weird.

00:12.080 --> 00:13.460
[ Roaring ]

00:13.460 --> 00:15.920
Do not be afraid.

00:15.920 --> 00:17.040
Super weird.

00:17.040 --> 00:18.710
Kevin?

00:18.710 --> 00:20.080
Yvette:
Haven't you always felt

00:20.080 --> 00:21.750
that you were meant
for something greater?

00:22.830 --> 00:24.250
Yeah, no.

00:24.250 --> 00:27.500
In every generation,
there are 36 righteous souls.

00:27.500 --> 00:29.540
You are the last
of the righteous.

00:29.540 --> 00:31.880
Initially,
I was reluctant to believe her.

00:31.880 --> 00:33.040
Who are you talking to?

00:33.040 --> 00:34.330
She can't see me.

00:34.330 --> 00:35.500
♪♪

00:35.500 --> 00:37.210
But she's done
a pretty good job

00:37.210 --> 00:38.830
convincing me she's real.

00:38.830 --> 00:40.830
I'm here to protect you.

00:40.830 --> 00:43.710
And now I have to do something
I haven't had to do before --

00:43.710 --> 00:47.080
put others before myself,
help people.

00:47.080 --> 00:49.710
I'm not a good person.

00:49.710 --> 00:52.250
But something has changed.

00:52.250 --> 00:54.250
I feel like I'm getting
a second chance.

00:54.250 --> 00:55.790
♪♪

00:55.790 --> 00:57.380
What just happened?
That guy...

00:57.380 --> 00:59.670
was wearing
so much Drakkar Noir.
[ Scoffs ]

00:59.670 --> 01:02.210
I am the last guy you'd
ever want to save the world,

01:02.210 --> 01:04.330
but I think
I can figure it out...

01:04.330 --> 01:05.250
probably.

01:07.620 --> 01:09.250
♪♪

01:09.250 --> 01:12.750
This world is full
of such beauty and grace,

01:12.750 --> 01:15.750
but most humans take it
for granted.

01:15.750 --> 01:18.250
They are unable
to truly experience

01:18.250 --> 01:19.960
the majesty all around them.

01:19.960 --> 01:22.790
[ Straining ]
That's 50.

01:22.790 --> 01:24.330
If you're gonna put me
through boot camp,

01:24.330 --> 01:27.670
can we at least share
your magic, invisible umbrella?

01:27.670 --> 01:30.040
Kevin, this is the start
of your spiritual training.
[ Grunts ]

01:30.040 --> 01:31.420
It doesn't feel
spiritual!

01:31.420 --> 01:34.170
It feels like...
wet push-ups! Ugh!

01:34.170 --> 01:36.620
Right now, you're learning
how to experience

01:36.620 --> 01:38.620
life's everyday
miracles,

01:38.620 --> 01:40.330
how to listen
to the Universe.

01:40.330 --> 01:41.420
[ Grunts ]

01:41.420 --> 01:43.120
Are you stoned?

01:43.120 --> 01:44.670
It's simple.

01:44.670 --> 01:45.960
The Universe will
guide you

01:45.960 --> 01:47.670
to those who are in need
of your help.

01:47.670 --> 01:49.880
That will build
your spiritual power.

01:49.880 --> 01:53.040
And, eventually, your spirit
will be strong enough

01:53.040 --> 01:54.880
to find the other righteous --
you got it?

01:54.880 --> 01:57.330
Can't you just give me a list
of the people I need to help?

01:57.330 --> 01:59.670
I'm a -- I'm a list guy.

01:59.670 --> 02:01.670
There are no lists,
Kevin.
Ugh!

02:01.670 --> 02:03.460
I know just as much
as you do.

02:03.460 --> 02:05.420
Now get up.
It's time for lunges.

02:05.420 --> 02:06.580
[ Breathing heavily ]

02:06.580 --> 02:10.120
Oh, no. I'm done.

02:10.120 --> 02:11.960
And, honestly,

02:11.960 --> 02:15.040
I don't think the Universe wants
to talk to me...at all.

02:15.040 --> 02:17.290
How are you feeling?

02:17.290 --> 02:19.620
Wet, exhausted.

02:19.620 --> 02:21.460
Good --
In moments like this,

02:21.460 --> 02:23.920
when you're too tired
to even think,

02:23.920 --> 02:26.040
that's when everything
falls away

02:26.040 --> 02:28.420
and things become
much clearer.

02:28.420 --> 02:32.710
[ Uplifting music plays ]

02:32.710 --> 02:42.210
♪♪

02:42.210 --> 02:44.460
[ Chimes tinkling ]

02:45.170 --> 02:52.040
♪♪

02:52.040 --> 02:54.210
Ah!

02:54.210 --> 02:56.120
[ Laughs ]

02:56.120 --> 02:58.580
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

02:58.580 --> 03:00.080
It's raining!

03:00.080 --> 03:02.080
It's raining on me!

03:02.080 --> 03:03.920
Ah! It's so wet.
Reese: Uh, Mom.

03:03.920 --> 03:05.380
Oh! Oh!

03:05.380 --> 03:08.040
[ Laughs manically ]

03:08.040 --> 03:09.580
Oh, my God!

03:09.580 --> 03:10.920
The rain is so wet!

03:10.920 --> 03:13.420
Oh! Oh, God!

03:13.420 --> 03:14.880
Look at it! Look at it!

03:20.000 --> 03:23.170
[ Alarm blaring ]

03:23.170 --> 03:26.380
♪ Welcome to your life ♪

03:26.380 --> 03:28.750
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

03:28.750 --> 03:31.540
♪ It could be a fantasy ♪
[ Groans ]

03:31.540 --> 03:33.620
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

03:33.620 --> 03:36.830
♪ Welcome to your world ♪

03:36.830 --> 03:38.710
♪ My girl ♪
[ Sniffs ]

03:38.710 --> 03:42.120
♪ Let it be your fantasy ♪

03:42.120 --> 03:44.580
♪ Oh, yeah ♪
[ Exhales sharply ]

03:44.580 --> 03:47.330
[ Music stops ]
Why so chipper?
It's 4:00 a.m.

03:47.330 --> 03:50.080
Good morning to you,
too.

03:50.080 --> 03:52.540
As I fell asleep last night,
I had this big idea.

03:52.540 --> 03:54.500
Oh, boy.
Do I want to hear this?

03:54.500 --> 03:56.540
You want me to listen
to the Universe, right?

03:56.540 --> 03:59.170
Uh, that's how you'll find the
people who need your help but...

03:59.170 --> 04:01.710
And listening is fine,
but it takes a lot of time,

04:01.710 --> 04:03.290
and I have a better plan.

04:03.290 --> 04:05.580
What if...
instead of waiting

04:05.580 --> 04:06.790
for the Universe
to guide me,

04:06.790 --> 04:09.460
I guide the Universe?

04:09.460 --> 04:12.040
No, I did not want
to hear this, Kevin.

04:12.040 --> 04:13.750
Don't worry.
I am all over it.

04:13.750 --> 04:17.290
Okay? Uh, now...

04:17.290 --> 04:19.710
"Auto."
Mm.

04:19.710 --> 04:23.710
This one's a little different
than I have but...
Mm.

04:23.710 --> 04:25.620
[ Insects chirping ]

04:25.620 --> 04:27.620
♪♪

04:27.620 --> 04:28.330
[ Printer whirring ]
Yeah.

04:28.330 --> 04:29.380
Kevin?

04:29.380 --> 04:31.880
♪♪

04:31.880 --> 04:34.170
What are you doing?
Sorry.
Did I wake you up?

04:34.170 --> 04:36.080
I just was getting a head start
on the day.

04:38.080 --> 04:41.790
"Need help? Call Kevin.
I'll do anything! Free!"

04:41.790 --> 04:43.830
Yep.
What the hell is this?

04:43.830 --> 04:45.080
It's just a project
I've been working on.

04:45.080 --> 04:47.040
I'm gonna hand these out
in town,

04:47.040 --> 04:49.170
uh...maybe do
some windshields.

04:49.170 --> 04:51.170
Okay.

04:51.170 --> 04:52.830
[ Printer beeps ]

04:52.830 --> 04:54.420
What's the plan?

04:54.420 --> 04:56.250
This.

04:56.250 --> 04:58.040
This is the plan.

04:58.040 --> 05:01.920
Look...

05:01.920 --> 05:04.380
Have you spoken
to your therapist?

05:04.380 --> 05:06.540
I...

05:06.540 --> 05:08.380
We traded voicemails.

05:08.380 --> 05:09.880
It was basically the same thing
as actually talking.

05:09.880 --> 05:11.460
Kevin...

05:11.460 --> 05:13.580
you've gone through something
really serious.

05:13.580 --> 05:15.330
You need to make getting better
a priority.

05:15.330 --> 05:16.670
I am.

05:16.670 --> 05:18.040
Really?
Mm-hmm.

05:18.040 --> 05:19.710
It's kind of hard
to believe that

05:19.710 --> 05:21.750
when you're up at 4:00 a.m.,
printing flyers that

05:21.750 --> 05:23.620
make you sound like
a prostitute.

05:23.620 --> 05:25.960
What? No, they...

05:25.960 --> 05:27.920
Oh! They kind of do,
don't they?

05:27.920 --> 05:29.540
A lot.

05:29.540 --> 05:32.120
Look, Kevin.
Mnh!

05:32.120 --> 05:34.460
Just put the flyers away.
Focus on yourself, okay?

05:34.460 --> 05:36.040
All over it.

05:36.040 --> 05:38.330
I'm going back to bed.

05:38.330 --> 05:39.540
[ Chair creaks lightly ]

05:41.210 --> 05:50.920
♪♪

05:50.920 --> 05:54.080
[ Marker scratching ]

05:54.080 --> 05:58.000
"No dirty stuff, please."

05:58.000 --> 06:00.000
Amy: You need to start
working on your science project

06:00.000 --> 06:02.670
tonight, okay --
no more procrastinating.

06:02.670 --> 06:04.000
Oh, and you need to work
on your scene

06:04.000 --> 06:05.380
for the play tryouts.
-I know.

06:05.380 --> 06:07.170
-"Aim." Hey.
-Yeah.

06:07.170 --> 06:09.620
Question -- can I borrow that
old truck in the garage?

06:09.620 --> 06:11.210
Uh, no.

06:11.210 --> 06:13.580
Uh, it's --
It's not running.

06:13.580 --> 06:15.540
Um...can I get a ride
with you guys?

06:15.540 --> 06:17.620
Yeah, well, we're leaving now.
Can you leave now?

06:17.620 --> 06:19.420
'Cause we're leaving right now.
Yes, I just need
to shower,

06:19.420 --> 06:20.960
Kevin,
we are leaving right now.
...brush my teeth,

06:20.960 --> 06:23.000
uh, iron a shirt maybe.
Come on.

06:23.000 --> 06:26.170
♪ Even the best-laid plans ♪

06:26.170 --> 06:28.460
♪ Come apart, comeback kid ♪
[ Spits ]

06:28.460 --> 06:30.580
Oh!
Gross.

06:30.580 --> 06:34.420
There's nothing gross about
proper dental care, okay?

06:34.420 --> 06:36.040
Hey, that truck is great.

06:36.040 --> 06:37.580
When do you think
it'll be fixed?

06:37.580 --> 06:38.920
Oh, uh, I don't know.

06:38.920 --> 06:40.540
[ Chuckling ]
Probably never.

06:40.540 --> 06:42.960
It needs a new carburetor.
I can't find one.

06:42.960 --> 06:45.880
Okay.
Call me if you need me.

06:45.880 --> 06:47.830
Hand these out
at school, okay?

06:47.830 --> 06:49.750
No, I told you not to do
the stupid flyer thing.
Bye! Thanks for the ride!

06:49.750 --> 06:51.330
Kevin.

06:51.330 --> 06:53.040
I told him not to do
the stupid flyer thing.

06:53.040 --> 06:54.620
[ Indistinct talking ]
Kevin.

06:54.620 --> 06:56.790
Oh, my God.
What is happening?

06:56.790 --> 06:59.000
He's not taking this
seriously.

06:59.000 --> 07:02.250
He's just weird.
I think he's doing okay.

07:02.250 --> 07:03.920
No. No.
You don't understand.

07:03.920 --> 07:05.040
I mean, what if this
is the same way

07:05.040 --> 07:07.790
that he behaved
before he...

07:07.790 --> 07:08.620
[ Sighs ]

07:08.620 --> 07:10.880
You know what?
You're right.

07:10.880 --> 07:12.250
He's fine.

07:12.250 --> 07:14.080
Let's get you to school.

07:14.080 --> 07:16.250
Free help --

07:16.250 --> 07:18.170
What a great idea!
[ Laughs ]

07:18.170 --> 07:20.120
It doesn't make me seem like
a prostitute, right?

07:20.120 --> 07:21.210
No!

07:21.210 --> 07:22.830
Prostitutes charge money.

07:22.830 --> 07:24.380
That's a great point.

07:24.380 --> 07:26.540
[ Chuckles ] Oh! Hey!

07:26.540 --> 07:28.830
I was talking to some
of the guys from high school.

07:28.830 --> 07:31.330
We were thinking
about getting together tonight.

07:31.330 --> 07:33.250
[ Chuckles ] Oh.
Little welcome-back party.

07:33.250 --> 07:35.170
Oh, I don't know.

07:35.170 --> 07:38.750
I -- It's been years since
I've seen anyone from school.

07:38.750 --> 07:41.080
Oh, I totally understand.
Totally.

07:41.080 --> 07:43.460
Okay.
Just gonna lose the deposit
on karaoke machine...

07:43.460 --> 07:45.290
Oh.
...and the booze luge

07:45.290 --> 07:46.920
and the second booze luge
for when the first one melts.

07:46.920 --> 07:48.880
But no biggie.

07:48.880 --> 07:51.290
Okay, I'll be there.

07:51.290 --> 07:53.000
Nice!
Let's do it.

07:53.000 --> 07:54.380
Hey, do you mind if I hand
some of these out

07:54.380 --> 07:55.710
to your customers?

07:55.710 --> 07:56.920
Dude...

07:56.920 --> 07:59.080
I'd be bummed
if you didn't.

07:59.080 --> 08:00.750
Awesome.

08:00.750 --> 08:02.250
I can help
with anything.

08:02.250 --> 08:03.330
Here you go, sir.

08:03.330 --> 08:04.500
Tell your friends.

08:04.500 --> 08:05.620
Can I...

08:07.670 --> 08:10.790
This is not listening.

08:10.790 --> 08:13.000
[ Hushed ] Yes, it is.
You said help people.

08:13.000 --> 08:14.830
Mnh-mnh. Mnh-mnh.

08:14.830 --> 08:17.580
I said listen
to the Universe.

08:17.580 --> 08:21.710
[ Clears throat ]

08:21.710 --> 08:23.040
I don't know
what that means.

08:23.040 --> 08:24.880
Look.

08:24.880 --> 08:27.290
You're trying,
and I applaud that.

08:27.290 --> 08:30.790
But handing out flyers is --
how should I put this? --

08:30.790 --> 08:33.380
so stupid it makes me sad.

08:33.380 --> 08:35.960
This is not a yard sale.

08:35.960 --> 08:37.120
This is something that
has never happened

08:37.120 --> 08:38.830
in the history
of humanity!

08:38.830 --> 08:41.330
But this
will get results.

08:41.330 --> 08:43.120
You know what? Fine.

08:43.120 --> 08:44.330
You go get your results.

08:44.330 --> 08:45.580
Fine.

08:45.580 --> 08:48.080
I-I will...go...

08:48.080 --> 08:49.250
get results.

08:49.250 --> 08:52.960
♪♪

08:52.960 --> 08:57.080
[ Breathes deeply ]

08:57.080 --> 08:58.710
Hey.

08:58.710 --> 09:01.380
[ Chuckles ]

09:01.380 --> 09:03.920
"Three Roads Brewery"?

09:03.920 --> 09:05.790
Come on, guys.
Don't hog the board.

09:05.790 --> 09:07.210
[ Inhales ]

09:07.210 --> 09:11.420
[ Wind blows ]
That's not...

09:11.420 --> 09:18.120
♪♪

09:18.120 --> 09:20.210
[ Sighs ]

09:20.210 --> 09:23.380
Okay! Who needs help?

09:23.380 --> 09:24.290
[ Tack clatters ]

09:24.290 --> 09:26.580
♪♪

09:26.580 --> 09:28.170
Hmm.

09:28.170 --> 09:30.670
It's on.

09:30.670 --> 09:33.500
Oh, no, no, no, don't!

09:33.500 --> 09:35.580
[ Breathes sharply ]

09:36.670 --> 09:39.380
"Three Roads Brewery"?
What the hell, man?

09:39.380 --> 09:41.210
Sorry. My bad.

09:41.210 --> 09:44.790
I-I didn't mean to, uh...
I was just trying...

09:46.880 --> 09:49.460
[ Clicks tongue ] Yep.

09:49.460 --> 09:51.670
Guess you got your results.

09:51.670 --> 09:54.040
[ Sighs ] Okay.

09:54.040 --> 09:57.080
♪♪

09:57.080 --> 10:00.170
♪ Honey, well,
you kept me waiting ♪

10:00.170 --> 10:01.670
♪ Honey, well,
you took a while ♪

10:01.670 --> 10:03.080
Hey, there.
Hey.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.500
Can I -- Can I help you
with something?

10:04.500 --> 10:08.170
Um...I'm not sure.

10:08.170 --> 10:10.790
Uh...

10:10.790 --> 10:12.380
Did you go
to La Salle High School?

10:12.380 --> 10:15.420
Oh. Yeah, yeah.
I, uh, graduated in 2002.

10:15.420 --> 10:17.080
I'm Jake Gilmore.
Kevin Finn. '99.

10:17.080 --> 10:18.380
Oh, no way!

10:18.380 --> 10:19.790
Wow! Okay.
Oh, that's really cool.

10:19.790 --> 10:21.790
Yeah, this place is
really cool.

10:21.790 --> 10:23.080
Ah, yeah, definitely,
if you're into beer.

10:23.080 --> 10:24.210
Know what I mean?
Yeah, yeah.

10:24.210 --> 10:26.040
Here, try this.

10:26.040 --> 10:27.830
Oh. Thank you.

10:27.830 --> 10:30.420
It's our House Stout,
brewed with roasted chicory.

10:30.420 --> 10:32.120
It's my grandfather's
recipe.

10:32.120 --> 10:34.120
Oh, wow. That is really good.
[ Chuckles ]

10:34.120 --> 10:36.790
Good. I'm glad you like it.
I'll leave you guys to talk.

10:36.790 --> 10:38.790
Thanks, Pop.
Thank you.
Enjoy.

10:38.790 --> 10:40.080
Uh, do you want to try
anything else?

10:40.080 --> 10:41.170
No, I-I think I'm good.

10:41.170 --> 10:44.790
Uh, actually,
I was wondering if, um...

10:44.790 --> 10:46.380
This will sound weird,

10:46.380 --> 10:50.670
but do you need...
any help with anything?

10:50.670 --> 10:52.380
Unfortunately,
I don't think my dad's looking

10:52.380 --> 10:53.830
to hire right now.

10:53.830 --> 10:55.250
[ Inhales sharply ]
No, sorry.

10:55.250 --> 10:57.210
I meant --
I meant do you --

10:57.210 --> 11:00.040
D-Do you any help
in your life?

11:00.040 --> 11:03.080
You know, like,
are you sad about anything?

11:03.080 --> 11:07.460
[ Laughs ] N--
Uh...no.
No?

11:07.460 --> 11:09.040
No.
Oh.

11:09.040 --> 11:11.330
Huh. Okay. Well, um...
are you married?

11:11.330 --> 11:13.250
Maybe there's some
relationship issues or...?

11:13.250 --> 11:14.710
Ooh! There could be
a dead relative

11:14.710 --> 11:16.750
that you haven't
gotten over?

11:16.750 --> 11:18.170
Credit-card debt?

11:18.170 --> 11:19.830
Drug addiction?
Gambling addiction?

11:19.830 --> 11:21.670
I-I-I have to get
back to work.

11:21.670 --> 11:22.960
'Cause even if you're winning,
it's still an addict--

11:22.960 --> 11:24.580
Wait. Hold on, hold on.
No, no. No.

11:24.580 --> 11:26.080
[ Chuckles ] Sorry,
you need my help.

11:26.080 --> 11:27.880
Something is wrong
with you.

11:27.880 --> 11:29.330
Bullying? Body issues?
Gluttony?

11:29.330 --> 11:30.920
Mm-hmm.
[ Breathes deeply ]

11:30.920 --> 11:32.290
You waste food. Laziness?
You waste water.

11:32.290 --> 11:35.210
Lust? You waste electricity?
Jealousy!

11:35.210 --> 11:37.500
You have a secret child.
Am I at least getting warm?

11:37.500 --> 11:38.830
You, um...
Oh.

11:38.830 --> 11:39.920
[ Whispering ]
You have trouble with the law.

11:39.920 --> 11:41.080
Is that it?

11:41.080 --> 11:42.580
Nate: Hi.

11:42.580 --> 11:44.670
Disturbance call came
over the radio?

11:44.670 --> 11:46.080
[ Normal voice ]
What? Me?

11:46.080 --> 11:48.170
No. Oh. But --
Okay, yeah.

11:48.170 --> 11:50.080
That makes sense.
Actually, we know each other.

11:50.080 --> 11:51.920
Uh, listen, I'm gonna think
about this some more.

11:51.920 --> 11:54.790
Don't even worry about it,
because I'm helping you, Jake!

11:59.000 --> 12:00.460
Kevin: Thank you
for giving me a ride home.

12:00.460 --> 12:02.250
I'm not a taxi service,
Kevin.
I know, I know.

12:02.250 --> 12:04.460
You can't just walk into
a place of business and
start accosting people.

12:04.460 --> 12:05.880
Yeah. I'm sorry.

12:05.880 --> 12:09.080
I-I was just trying
to figure out how to be helpful.

12:09.080 --> 12:10.540
By not doing that.

12:10.540 --> 12:13.080
Right, right.

12:13.080 --> 12:15.170
Um, thanks again, Nate.

12:15.170 --> 12:17.380
Hopefully,
Amy will fix her truck soon,

12:17.380 --> 12:19.080
and then I can
just drive that.

12:19.080 --> 12:20.920
What's wrong with it?

12:20.920 --> 12:23.460
Um...she said something
about a carburetor.

12:23.460 --> 12:24.380
Is that a car thing?

12:24.380 --> 12:25.960
I might know a guy.

12:25.960 --> 12:27.330
Oh, awesome.
That's be great.

12:27.330 --> 12:28.540
Thanks.

12:28.540 --> 12:30.750
[ Door closes ]
Hey, uh...

12:30.750 --> 12:32.380
a bunch of us are
getting together tonight

12:32.380 --> 12:33.750
at Frankie's if --
if you want to --

12:33.750 --> 12:36.500
All right.
See you tonight, buddy!

12:36.500 --> 12:38.580
[ Owl hooting,
crickets chirping ]

12:38.580 --> 12:42.540
♪♪

12:42.540 --> 12:45.000
A cream cheese
and jelly sandwich?

12:45.000 --> 12:48.500
What...?
Are you in preschool?

12:48.500 --> 12:49.540
Now you're here.

12:49.540 --> 12:51.250
It's great timing.

12:51.250 --> 12:53.920
You show up after
you let the Universe

12:53.920 --> 12:55.500
toss me in the back
of a police car.

12:55.500 --> 12:59.170
I let a police officer toss you
in the back of a police car.

12:59.170 --> 13:01.290
My job is to keep you alive.

13:01.290 --> 13:02.960
You look alive to me.

13:02.960 --> 13:05.670
Dumb but alive.

13:05.670 --> 13:09.040
So mean.

13:09.040 --> 13:10.420
Look, I think,
if we're gonna be a team,

13:10.420 --> 13:12.420
we need to work
on how we treat each other.

13:12.420 --> 13:13.880
We're not a team.

13:13.880 --> 13:16.670
Um...
we absolutely are.

13:16.670 --> 13:18.830
We're like Good Cop,

13:18.830 --> 13:21.710
Angel...Cop.

13:21.710 --> 13:23.920
Maybe it would help
if, um...

13:23.920 --> 13:25.830
if I knew a little bit
more about you.

13:25.830 --> 13:27.880
Like, what did you do
before you came down here?

13:27.880 --> 13:29.420
You don't need to know
anything about me.

13:29.420 --> 13:31.620
You need to focus
on helping Jake.

13:31.620 --> 13:33.670
But...[Sighs]

13:33.670 --> 13:36.120
But I don't know anything
about anything.

13:36.120 --> 13:40.790
Like, what happened to the rest
of the 36 righteous?

13:40.790 --> 13:42.580
[ Clears throat ]
We're not sure.

13:42.580 --> 13:43.960
By the time
we all arrived...

13:43.960 --> 13:47.250
you were the only one left.

13:47.250 --> 13:48.620
And so I'm pretty
amazing.

13:48.620 --> 13:50.210
You're a real hero.
Mm.

13:50.210 --> 13:52.210
But I don't like
to really talk about it.

13:52.210 --> 13:54.170
I'm just sort of silent --
quiet, silent hero type.

13:54.170 --> 13:56.330
Mm. Humility.
So humble.

13:56.330 --> 13:57.960
I can tell.

13:57.960 --> 14:01.500
I know. I know I...

14:01.500 --> 14:02.540
I know I shouldn't.

14:02.540 --> 14:04.250
It just...

14:04.250 --> 14:06.880
You know, just --
Amy?

14:06.880 --> 14:08.920
Kevin. Hey.

14:08.920 --> 14:09.880
[ Grunts ]

14:09.880 --> 14:11.120
Hey.

14:11.120 --> 14:14.080
Who are you, uh...
talking to?

14:14.080 --> 14:17.460
What? Um...no one.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

14:17.460 --> 14:18.830
I was talking to myself.

14:18.830 --> 14:20.290
Why are you
all dressed up?

14:20.290 --> 14:23.000
Oh, um...

14:23.000 --> 14:24.790
T-Tyler's having
a little get-together tonight.

14:24.790 --> 14:26.170
You want to come?
No, I can't.

14:26.170 --> 14:28.790
It's a school night.
All right.

14:28.790 --> 14:31.460
I mean, honestly,
a-a party doesn't sound

14:31.460 --> 14:32.960
like a good idea
for you either.

14:32.960 --> 14:34.460
Really? Why not?

14:34.460 --> 14:36.960
Well, it just --
you know, it's a lot.

14:36.960 --> 14:38.580
A lot of people there
from your past

14:38.580 --> 14:40.170
and...I don't know.

14:40.170 --> 14:41.710
They're gonna ask a lot
of questions about

14:41.710 --> 14:42.960
what you've been up to,
and it's just --

14:42.960 --> 14:46.210
it could be
a stressful situation

14:46.210 --> 14:50.710
for someone who's been through
what you've been through.

14:50.710 --> 14:52.830
You know,
you don't have to, um...

14:52.830 --> 14:54.420
[Chuckling]
talk around it.

14:54.420 --> 14:55.830
What?

14:55.830 --> 14:58.420
What -- What --
What I did, um...

14:58.420 --> 15:00.460
I'm okay talking about it,

15:00.460 --> 15:02.750
um...unless it makes you
uncomfortable.

15:02.750 --> 15:04.460
No, it doesn't make me
uncomfortable.

15:04.460 --> 15:07.040
Okay, then what's
with the egg shells?

15:07.040 --> 15:10.250
All right. Um...

15:10.250 --> 15:14.120
I'm scared that you're gonna try
to kill yourself again.

15:14.120 --> 15:17.330
Oh, uh...

15:17.330 --> 15:19.670
Yeah. Yeah,
before you got here,

15:19.670 --> 15:21.420
I went through your room
to make sure that there was

15:21.420 --> 15:24.580
nothing in there that you could
use to hurt yourself with.

15:24.580 --> 15:26.620
Forgot my Alamo
letter opener.

15:26.620 --> 15:29.380
You know, I'm glad that
you think this is funny.
Okay, I'm sorry.

15:29.380 --> 15:31.330
I didn't mean to make
less of what I...

15:31.330 --> 15:32.790
what I did.

15:32.790 --> 15:35.380
But as responsible as
you feel for me,

15:35.380 --> 15:37.170
uh...[ Sighs ]

15:37.170 --> 15:38.830
It's --
It isn't just about you.

15:38.830 --> 15:41.750
I need to be responsible for me,
too, you know?

15:41.750 --> 15:44.120
[ Vehicle approaches,
horn honking ]

15:44.120 --> 15:45.580
It's...

15:45.580 --> 15:47.170
It's Tyler.
Yeah.

15:47.170 --> 15:49.710
Go.

15:49.710 --> 15:51.250
Go.

15:51.250 --> 15:52.750
Have fun.

15:52.750 --> 15:54.580
Tyler: Karaoke action!

15:54.580 --> 15:58.170
Let's do it!

15:58.170 --> 16:00.210
All right.

16:00.210 --> 16:02.880
♪♪

16:02.880 --> 16:04.830
[ Rock music plays
in background ]

16:04.830 --> 16:07.420
[ Chuckling ] Whoa.
You look exactly the same.

16:07.420 --> 16:09.000
Oh. [ Laughs ]

16:09.000 --> 16:11.080
I had such a crush on,

16:11.080 --> 16:12.830
like, three of your friends
in high school.

16:12.830 --> 16:14.710
[ Chuckles ]
Cool.

16:14.710 --> 16:17.000
Yeah.
That's cool.

16:17.000 --> 16:19.290
So, I heard you're moving
back here?

16:19.290 --> 16:21.620
Um, yeah.

16:21.620 --> 16:23.420
Are you crazy?
No.

16:23.420 --> 16:25.920
Why would you want
to leave New York?

16:25.920 --> 16:28.790
Oh, there's, uh, um...
a bunch of reasons.

16:28.790 --> 16:30.880
Thank you. Um...

16:30.880 --> 16:32.750
It just, uh...

16:34.420 --> 16:36.710
Oh. Would you excuse me
for a minute?

16:38.250 --> 16:39.830
What are you
doing here?

16:39.830 --> 16:42.710
Your species is able
to express joy

16:42.710 --> 16:44.790
in some amazing ways --

16:44.790 --> 16:49.000
music, dance,
celebrations like this.

16:49.000 --> 16:51.210
Ahh!

16:51.210 --> 16:53.250
Hey, what?
You're not into it?

16:53.250 --> 16:55.580
No, I-I-I am.

16:55.580 --> 16:57.460
Amy was right, though.

16:57.460 --> 16:59.250
Everybody's asking
why I'm here.

16:59.250 --> 17:00.960
And...?

17:00.960 --> 17:03.500
[ Chuckling ]
And I guarantee

17:03.500 --> 17:05.170
they don't really want
to know the answer.

17:05.170 --> 17:08.290
Look, you want to know
more about me.

17:08.290 --> 17:10.080
Mm-hmm.
Why?

17:10.080 --> 17:13.380
So -- So you can
feel comfortable with me.

17:13.380 --> 17:15.330
That's how you connect
with people.

17:15.330 --> 17:17.750
You -- You share a little bit
of yourself with them.

17:17.750 --> 17:18.710
Right?

17:18.710 --> 17:22.210
I-I don't know. I...

17:22.210 --> 17:25.000
You don't know what?

17:25.000 --> 17:28.420
I, um, don't know
why you'd want

17:28.420 --> 17:30.170
to come to this party,
but here you are.
Uh...

17:30.170 --> 17:31.460
Thanks, man.
Oh, you know what?
Here, let me --

17:31.460 --> 17:32.750
Let me get this. Uh...

17:32.750 --> 17:33.790
Oh, you don't have
to do that.

17:33.790 --> 17:36.580
No, I'm sorry about today.

17:36.580 --> 17:39.120
And thank you for coming.

17:39.120 --> 17:40.500
Thank -- Thank you.

17:40.500 --> 17:41.670
[ Chuckles ]

17:41.670 --> 17:44.420
And welcome home.

17:44.420 --> 17:45.420
[ Chuckles ]

17:47.380 --> 17:48.750
You were in New York,
right?
[ Breathes deeply ]

17:48.750 --> 17:50.460
What made you
come back?

17:50.460 --> 17:51.920
Oh, uh...

17:51.920 --> 17:54.750
I just wanted a change.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

17:54.750 --> 17:59.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:59.210 --> 18:01.670
Um...

18:01.670 --> 18:03.580
I...

18:03.580 --> 18:05.960
hated my life.

18:05.960 --> 18:10.460
Why?

18:10.460 --> 18:13.960
I had all these things
that...

18:13.960 --> 18:16.620
great job, great car,
great apartment,

18:16.620 --> 18:20.080
and it -- it --
it didn't matter.

18:20.080 --> 18:23.380
I-I was miserable.
Hmm.

18:23.380 --> 18:27.380
And I felt like a jerk
for being miserable.

18:27.380 --> 18:29.460
Uh, I...

18:29.460 --> 18:32.500
I was trapped.

18:32.500 --> 18:36.290
Yeah,
I've felt like that.

18:36.290 --> 18:38.620
My dad wakes up every morning
thinking about beer.

18:38.620 --> 18:40.460
It's -- It's, um...

18:40.460 --> 18:42.620
It's his passion.

18:42.620 --> 18:44.580
I hate beer so much.

18:44.580 --> 18:46.210
Oh, wow.

18:46.210 --> 18:48.460
I hate lagers and stouts,
pilsners and ports

18:48.460 --> 18:50.620
and doppelbocks
and hefeweizens.

18:50.620 --> 18:52.380
Ugh!
Hefeweizen is so gross.

18:52.380 --> 18:54.290
I hate it.
I hate everything about beer.

18:54.290 --> 18:56.500
You don't like beer.
Not even the littlest bit.

18:56.500 --> 18:58.080
Yeah, totally get it.
[ Chuckles ]

18:58.080 --> 19:00.040
Um, well, if you --

19:00.040 --> 19:03.500
if you could do another job,
what would it be?

19:03.500 --> 19:05.040
First thing that
comes to your mind.

19:05.040 --> 19:06.880
It doesn't --
It doesn't matter, man.

19:06.880 --> 19:08.500
It doesn't -- It doesn't --
You know, I'm -- I'm --

19:08.500 --> 19:12.540
I'm an only child, and so,
if I don't do it, then...

19:12.540 --> 19:14.330
the family business
is gone.

19:14.330 --> 19:16.120
Look, that's...

19:16.120 --> 19:18.920
That's hard, but I...
Yeah.

19:18.920 --> 19:20.290
I'm pretty sure your dad
wouldn't want you

19:20.290 --> 19:22.710
to be miserable.

19:22.710 --> 19:24.790
Talk to him.

19:24.790 --> 19:27.330
Listen,
it's not a bad life.

19:27.330 --> 19:29.540
It's just not
the one I wanted.

19:29.540 --> 19:30.960
Tyler: All right!
[ Feedback ]

19:30.960 --> 19:33.500
Since I'm the only one
who signed up,

19:33.500 --> 19:36.500
I guess I'm gonna get
this party started!

19:36.500 --> 19:37.670
[ Cheers and applause ]
[ Chuckles ]

19:37.670 --> 19:40.040
Kevin, welcome home, buddy.

19:40.040 --> 19:42.580
This one's for you.

19:42.580 --> 19:43.830
[ Electricity crackling ]
[ Bar patrons groan ]

19:43.830 --> 19:45.210
No! No, no, no!

19:45.210 --> 19:46.540
Aw!
[ Bar patrons murmur ]

19:46.540 --> 19:47.620
[ Electricity crackling,
feedback ]

19:47.620 --> 19:48.830
[ Bar patrons groaning ]
Aw.

19:48.830 --> 19:50.120
Man: Aw, Tyler!

19:50.120 --> 19:52.460
[ Blows, slurping ]

19:52.460 --> 19:55.000
Aw, not again!
Not again. [ Laughs ]

19:55.000 --> 19:56.960
Jake, don't you owe it
to yourself

19:56.960 --> 20:00.290
to at least start a dialogue
with your dad?

20:00.290 --> 20:01.750
You don't have to
dump it on him all at once,

20:01.750 --> 20:03.170
but...
[ Sighs ]

20:03.170 --> 20:04.710
maybe tell him
you need a little break.

20:04.710 --> 20:07.460
I guess. I don't know.

20:07.460 --> 20:09.250
You want a little
moral support?

20:09.250 --> 20:11.920
'Cause I can come with.

20:11.920 --> 20:14.710
Yeah, that'd be good.
Thanks.

20:14.710 --> 20:15.960
Okay!

20:15.960 --> 20:18.540
Let's get this party
restarted!

20:18.540 --> 20:22.540
Who knows how to fix
a karaoke machine?

20:22.540 --> 20:26.290
[ Fort Atlantic's
"Just Hold On" plays ]

20:28.960 --> 20:31.750
So, you're like a handyman that
doesn't charge any money?

20:31.750 --> 20:33.500
Kristin.
Hey.

20:33.500 --> 20:35.330
[ Chuckles ]
Seems like a bad
business model.

20:35.330 --> 20:37.500
Oh, it is the worst.

20:37.500 --> 20:41.000
But I would be happy to offer
you my services anytime.

20:41.000 --> 20:42.750
Oh, well, you always
were a gentleman.

20:42.750 --> 20:44.120
[ Chuckles ] Well, then,
why did your mom hate me

20:44.120 --> 20:45.750
when we were dating?

20:45.750 --> 20:47.710
She, uh --
She thought you were too smooth.

20:47.710 --> 20:50.080
Was I?
Oh, yeah.

20:50.080 --> 20:51.460
[ Clicks tongue ]

20:51.460 --> 20:54.540
But, um...

20:54.540 --> 20:55.880
there was a lot to like.

20:57.710 --> 20:59.540
Well, there was a lot to like
with you, too.

21:03.250 --> 21:05.000
So, um....

21:05.000 --> 21:07.540
So, talk to me about the --
you know, the services.

21:07.540 --> 21:10.000
What -- What exactly c--
is it that you can do?

21:10.000 --> 21:14.330
Uh, well, just like it says,
I can do anything.

21:14.330 --> 21:16.790
Electrical.
Uh, no.

21:16.790 --> 21:18.710
[ Laughing ] I have no idea
what I'm doing here.

21:18.710 --> 21:20.620
What about plumbing?

21:20.620 --> 21:21.580
Um...no.

21:21.580 --> 21:23.000
Yuck. No way.

21:23.000 --> 21:24.830
Ugh.

21:24.830 --> 21:27.380
Could you change
a hard-to-reach light bulb?

21:29.040 --> 21:30.710
Maybe.

21:30.710 --> 21:32.580
Um...

21:32.580 --> 21:35.750
I really would have to see it
to be sure.

21:35.750 --> 21:39.420
♪ I speak these words ♪

21:39.420 --> 21:43.380
♪ With an autumn tone ♪
It doesn't matter.

21:43.380 --> 21:45.830
Aaaah!
[ Glass shatters ]

21:45.830 --> 21:47.170
I definitely
can't fix that.

21:47.170 --> 21:48.380
[ Chuckles ]

21:53.170 --> 21:54.790
I know.
I know he's an adult.

21:54.790 --> 21:56.830
But it would still be nice
if he returned a text.
Mom?

21:56.830 --> 21:59.120
Reese. [ Sighs ]

21:59.120 --> 21:59.960
Geez.

21:59.960 --> 22:01.420
Don't do that.

22:01.420 --> 22:03.250
What are you doing up?

22:03.250 --> 22:04.750
Heard you out here.

22:04.750 --> 22:07.330
You only stay up late
when you worry.

22:07.330 --> 22:08.500
Sweetheart.
[ Chuckles ]

22:08.500 --> 22:10.710
I'm okay.

22:10.710 --> 22:14.000
Kevin's probably just out
doing something stupid.

22:14.000 --> 22:16.670
I know. I know.

22:16.670 --> 22:18.580
Now, go on. Bed.

22:18.580 --> 22:19.710
It's a school night.

22:19.710 --> 22:22.210
School night for you,
too.

22:22.210 --> 22:23.920
[ Dog barking in distance ]

22:23.920 --> 22:25.830
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

22:25.830 --> 22:28.080
All right.
You're right.

22:28.080 --> 22:29.960
I don't know how I'm gonna sleep
until he gets home,

22:29.960 --> 22:31.290
but I will try.

22:31.290 --> 22:35.620
Mom...everything's
gonna be fine.

22:35.620 --> 22:37.330
[ Switch clicks ]
Come on.

22:37.330 --> 22:38.620
[ Insects chirping ]

22:38.620 --> 22:43.120
♪♪

22:43.120 --> 22:45.000
[ Dog barking in distance ]

22:45.000 --> 22:53.830
♪♪

22:53.830 --> 22:55.460
Kristen:
[ Laughing ] My God.

22:55.460 --> 22:58.080
Look at you.
You're a baby.

22:58.080 --> 23:01.580
You said that I would
regret this vest.

23:01.580 --> 23:03.750
[ Chuckles ] I get embarrassed
every time I look at it.

23:03.750 --> 23:05.880
I wish I still had
this vest.

23:05.880 --> 23:07.290
I would be wearing that vest
right now,

23:07.290 --> 23:09.880
just no pants, gold vest.
[ Laughs ]

23:09.880 --> 23:12.580
Oh, man.
Amy and Jon.

23:12.580 --> 23:15.880
Oh. God.
He made her so happy.

23:15.880 --> 23:18.500
Yeah. I swear,
he looked at her like that

23:18.500 --> 23:20.750
every day
they were together.

23:20.750 --> 23:22.670
♪ So finish your
whiskey or beer ♪
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

23:22.670 --> 23:24.960
Um...not me.

23:24.960 --> 23:27.920
Oh.
♪ Closing time ♪

23:27.920 --> 23:30.120
♪ You don't have to go home ♪

23:30.120 --> 23:32.750
Oh, shoot.
What's wrong?

23:32.750 --> 23:34.500
Uh, uh, nothing.
I just --

23:34.500 --> 23:36.500
I forgot to let my sister
know where I was,

23:36.500 --> 23:38.080
and she, um...

23:38.080 --> 23:39.670
called and
texted a lot.

23:39.670 --> 23:41.000
[ Chuckles ] I'll just --
I'll just let her know

23:41.000 --> 23:43.120
that I'll be
sleeping elsewhere.

23:43.120 --> 23:46.830
Oh, no, no, go home,
and then she won't be worried.

23:46.830 --> 23:49.330
Oh. Okay.
I mean, I'm fine to stay.

23:49.330 --> 23:50.580
Yeah, no, I know.
I just -- I, uh...

23:50.580 --> 23:52.920
I have yoga super early.
Oh.

23:52.920 --> 23:57.000
And was not expecting to host
a sleepover so...
Okay.

23:57.000 --> 23:59.080
[ Both laugh ]
♪ Closing time ♪

23:59.080 --> 24:01.250
Um...

24:01.250 --> 24:02.790
Ooh, pants.

24:02.790 --> 24:04.460
♪ ...to the places
you will be -- ♪

24:04.460 --> 24:06.790
[ Insects chirping ]

24:06.790 --> 24:09.170
Well, well, well!

24:09.170 --> 24:10.460
Mm.

24:10.460 --> 24:12.170
Somebody's happy!

24:12.170 --> 24:15.250
Don't even try to guilt me
about this, okay?

24:15.250 --> 24:17.380
I really like her. So...
Wow!

24:17.380 --> 24:20.460
Humans are weird
about sex.
What?

24:20.460 --> 24:22.080
I mean,
millions of years,

24:22.080 --> 24:24.120
and you have the same hang-ups
you've always had?

24:24.120 --> 24:27.080
If it's consenting adults,
I don't care.
This is uncomfortable.

24:27.080 --> 24:29.170
Talking about this with you
is uncomfortable.

24:29.170 --> 24:31.380
And you still haven't figured
out the right way to do it.

24:31.380 --> 24:33.420
There's a right way?

24:33.420 --> 24:36.330
Oh, such a waste.

24:36.330 --> 24:37.830
Tell me the right way.

24:37.830 --> 24:38.830
Reese: Kevin!

24:38.830 --> 24:40.040
Reese!

24:40.040 --> 24:43.210
What are you doing
out here?

24:43.210 --> 24:46.380
Stop it!
Stop acting crazy!
Hmm? I'm not!

24:46.380 --> 24:47.670
You're having arguments
with nobody

24:47.670 --> 24:49.750
in the middle
of the street!

24:49.750 --> 24:51.580
Well, sure. Okay.

24:51.580 --> 24:54.330
You stay out all night,
and you don't even call my mom?

24:54.330 --> 24:56.920
And you know
what she's like.
Yes, I know. I'm sorry.

24:56.920 --> 24:59.880
Kevin, if you're gonna stay,
you have to stop worrying her.

24:59.880 --> 25:03.120
You have to act
like a normal person.

25:03.120 --> 25:05.960
Do you even know how
to act normal?

25:05.960 --> 25:07.710
[ Sighs ]

25:07.710 --> 25:10.170
I can probably
figure it out.

25:10.170 --> 25:13.080
Uh...

25:13.080 --> 25:16.040
Here, come on. Let's --
Let's get you home.

25:16.040 --> 25:17.540
Okay?

25:17.540 --> 25:19.500
[ Chirping continues ]

25:24.170 --> 25:25.670
♪♪

25:25.670 --> 25:29.460
Look at that.

25:29.460 --> 25:32.330
[ Chuckling ] Awesome.

25:32.330 --> 25:35.620
Just like
every other night.

25:35.620 --> 25:38.880
It is.

25:38.880 --> 25:40.330
[ Sighs ]

25:40.330 --> 25:43.120
♪♪

25:43.120 --> 25:45.460
Dad.

25:45.460 --> 25:47.380
I know how much
this means to you,

25:47.380 --> 25:50.330
but I've been feeling really
burnt out lately, and I...

25:51.670 --> 25:53.380
[ Sighing ]
I think I need a break.

25:54.380 --> 25:55.500
Good.
Yeah?

25:55.500 --> 25:58.120
Yeah, keep it simple.
Um, ease in.

25:58.120 --> 26:00.330
Just -- Just trying to get
the conversation started.

26:00.330 --> 26:01.670
That's right.
Yeah.

26:01.670 --> 26:03.120
Okay.
All right.

26:03.120 --> 26:04.210
I'm going in.

26:04.210 --> 26:05.750
Go get 'em.

26:08.620 --> 26:10.790
[ Sighs ]

26:10.790 --> 26:13.710
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:13.710 --> 26:15.500
Kristin.

26:15.500 --> 26:18.170
Hey.
Hey. Hi.

26:18.170 --> 26:20.380
I was, um --
I was gonna call you

26:20.380 --> 26:23.000
to see if you wanted
to grab dinner tonight.

26:23.000 --> 26:26.250
Oh, yeah, no thanks.
I'm good.

26:26.250 --> 26:27.500
You're good?

26:27.500 --> 26:30.540
Okay, um, well,
what about tomorrow night?

26:30.540 --> 26:31.620
Yeah,
I don't think so.

26:34.000 --> 26:35.710
Wait, did I --
did I do something wrong?

26:35.710 --> 26:37.170
No, no, no.
No? Okay.

26:37.170 --> 26:39.120
I just -- I-I mean,
you know, 'cause, I...

26:39.120 --> 26:40.960
[ Scoffing ] Come on,
we're not gonna --

26:40.960 --> 26:42.710
we're not gonna
do this again, right?

26:42.710 --> 26:44.500
Well...why?

26:44.500 --> 26:47.000
I mean, we -- we --
we broke up years ago,

26:47.000 --> 26:48.330
but that doesn't mean
that we c--
We didn't break up.

26:50.790 --> 26:53.580
Um, I-I-I
don't understand.

26:53.580 --> 26:55.620
We didn't break up.

26:55.620 --> 26:57.540
Mm...

26:57.540 --> 26:59.380
You went away
to college, and, uh,

26:59.380 --> 27:01.080
we talked a few --
a few times.

27:01.080 --> 27:03.830
And then I left
you a couple messages,

27:03.830 --> 27:05.710
and you
never called me back.

27:05.710 --> 27:07.330
So I got the message.

27:10.120 --> 27:13.120
Oh. Wow.
That's terrible.

27:13.120 --> 27:14.880
[ Chuckles ]
I'm -- I'm terrible.

27:14.880 --> 27:17.330
Kevin.
I'm not mad.

27:17.330 --> 27:19.880
I'm -- I'm not even
hurt anymore.

27:19.880 --> 27:22.420
It was a --
It was a long time ago.

27:22.420 --> 27:25.540
[ Inhales sharply ]
But I-I-I-I didn't mean -- I --

27:25.540 --> 27:27.920
Oh, you know,
I actually --

27:27.920 --> 27:31.460
I got to --
I got to run, okay?

27:31.460 --> 27:33.120
Okay.

27:37.000 --> 27:38.460
Kevin!

27:44.120 --> 27:46.290
I did it.
I quit. I'm done.
Yeah?

27:46.290 --> 27:48.620
That's great.
Oh, wait. You what?

27:48.620 --> 27:50.000
I thought you were gonna
start slow,

27:50.000 --> 27:52.290
maybe work up to the --
No, you inspired me.

27:52.290 --> 27:54.120
You -- I, uh -- I, uh --
This is my life.

27:54.120 --> 27:56.290
It's the only one I get. I got
to follow my heart, right?

27:56.290 --> 27:57.580
Yeah, yeah.
I mean,
that's what you said. That's --

27:57.580 --> 27:59.080
Yeah. Yeah, for sure.

27:59.080 --> 28:00.670
How did -- How did your --
How did your dad take it?

28:00.670 --> 28:01.880
Oh, no,
that was the best part.

28:01.880 --> 28:03.500
I mean, he --
he seemed, uh...

28:03.500 --> 28:05.710
He seemed really
totally cool with it.

28:05.710 --> 28:07.250
Oh.
[ Laughing ] I know.

28:07.250 --> 28:08.500
Fantastic.
Right?

28:08.500 --> 28:10.170
[ Grunts ]
Oh, my gosh.

28:10.170 --> 28:11.500
Oh, no.

28:11.500 --> 28:13.170
♪♪

28:13.170 --> 28:15.000
Dad!

28:15.000 --> 28:16.500
Dad?

28:16.500 --> 28:19.120
Blood pressure's elevated.
Checking vitals.

28:19.120 --> 28:20.920
[ Radio chatter ]

28:20.920 --> 28:22.710
This is all your fault.

28:22.710 --> 28:24.210
[ Doors close ]
[ Siren wailing ]

28:24.210 --> 28:26.580
♪♪

28:30.380 --> 28:32.330
♪♪

28:32.330 --> 28:33.670
[ Creaks ]

28:34.670 --> 28:41.750
♪♪

28:41.750 --> 28:43.960
Where are you going?
Home.

28:43.960 --> 28:45.620
No, you need to
go to the hospital.

28:45.620 --> 28:47.790
The Universe
just gave you a sign

28:47.790 --> 28:49.540
by giving you
an actual sign.

28:49.540 --> 28:52.290
Well, the Universe just made me
give Jake's dad a heart attack,

28:52.290 --> 28:54.420
so the Universe can bite me
because I am done.

28:54.420 --> 28:55.920
That's not how this works.

28:55.920 --> 28:57.380
You made a mistake.

28:57.380 --> 28:59.380
I'm not one of the 36,
so go find someone else.

28:59.380 --> 29:00.830
You cannot
ignore me, Kevin.

29:00.830 --> 29:02.210
You cannot
ignore the Universe!

29:02.210 --> 29:03.670
See, that's where
you're wrong

29:03.670 --> 29:04.960
because I am great
at ignoring things.

29:04.960 --> 29:06.880
I've been ignoring things
for my whole life!

29:06.880 --> 29:08.080
[ Tires screech ]

29:08.080 --> 29:09.620
Woman: Aah!
Man: Hospital!

29:09.620 --> 29:11.210
Ooh! Oh, my God!
Which way to the hospital?!

29:11.210 --> 29:13.420
[ Woman screaming ]

29:13.420 --> 29:15.040
[ Tires screech ]

29:15.040 --> 29:17.880
♪♪

29:17.880 --> 29:21.330
[ Sirens wailing ]

29:21.330 --> 29:23.170
♪♪

29:23.170 --> 29:24.460
Ignoring!

29:24.460 --> 29:26.080
So much ignoring.

29:26.080 --> 29:28.290
♪♪

29:28.290 --> 29:30.500
Done?
Okay.

29:30.500 --> 29:32.250
What?

29:32.250 --> 29:35.250
Oh, don't get mad,
Kevin.

29:35.250 --> 29:36.460
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:36.460 --> 29:38.420
Student: That's crazy.

29:38.420 --> 29:39.620
Student #2: That's cool.

29:40.670 --> 29:43.000
Amy?

29:43.000 --> 29:44.750
Nate.

29:44.750 --> 29:46.710
Is everything okay?

29:46.710 --> 29:49.040
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, everything's fine.

29:49.040 --> 29:51.420
Oh. [ Sighs ]
Okay.

29:51.420 --> 29:53.540
'Cause the last thing you want
is a surprise visit from a cop.

29:53.540 --> 29:56.000
[ Chuckles ]

29:56.000 --> 29:59.790
But, I mean,
you're great.

29:59.790 --> 30:01.620
Uh...hi.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

30:01.620 --> 30:04.080
Hi.

30:04.080 --> 30:06.790
So, I spoke with
a guy at our impound lot

30:06.790 --> 30:08.880
who knows a guy
down in Colton.

30:08.880 --> 30:11.540
Kevin said you needed
a carburetor for your truck.

30:11.540 --> 30:13.790
So here it is.

30:16.250 --> 30:19.920
It's rebuilt.
I-I hope that's okay.

30:19.920 --> 30:21.040
Yeah.

30:21.040 --> 30:22.580
It, um -- It's great.

30:22.580 --> 30:24.540
[ Chuckles ] Thank you.

30:24.540 --> 30:26.960
Um...

30:26.960 --> 30:29.040
I got a class
across campus,

30:29.040 --> 30:30.960
so I've got to run,
but thanks, Nate.

30:35.420 --> 30:39.040
[ Breathes deeply ]

30:39.040 --> 30:41.540
Earlier today,
an apparent heart attack

30:41.540 --> 30:44.670
sent the man to the hospital,
where he is expected to under--

30:44.670 --> 30:46.960
Announcer: Side effects
may include hallucinations,

30:46.960 --> 30:49.380
heart attack that will require
hospitalization --

30:49.380 --> 30:50.750
[ TV clicks off ]
[ Sighs ]

31:00.670 --> 31:03.040
[ Birds chirping ]

31:05.040 --> 31:07.040
Hey,
is this a carburetor?

31:07.040 --> 31:08.710
Where'd you get it?

31:12.120 --> 31:13.670
Is everything okay?

31:13.670 --> 31:15.040
Fine.

31:15.040 --> 31:17.080
Oh.

31:17.080 --> 31:19.710
All right.

31:19.710 --> 31:21.460
You know
what would be great?

31:21.460 --> 31:23.830
For you not to tell
everybody about my business.

31:23.830 --> 31:26.750
Um, what are
you talking about?

31:26.750 --> 31:28.210
Nate brought that
to school.

31:28.210 --> 31:30.670
He said that
you told him all about it.

31:30.670 --> 31:33.670
And this makes you
supper happy?

31:33.670 --> 31:36.000
I didn't ask you to do that,
Kevin.

31:36.000 --> 31:38.040
Worry about yourself.

31:38.040 --> 31:40.210
Okay,
am I missing something?

31:40.210 --> 31:41.710
Or are you
actually upset

31:41.710 --> 31:43.920
because someone did something
nice for you?

31:43.920 --> 31:47.040
No, I'm upset because you're not
taking care of yourself.

31:47.040 --> 31:48.960
[ Sighs ] Amy,
I love you,

31:48.960 --> 31:51.210
but you are just
as messed up as I am.

31:51.210 --> 31:52.710
Oh, that's hilarious.

31:52.710 --> 31:54.040
You try to control
everybody else's life,

31:54.040 --> 31:55.250
but you are
out of control.

31:55.250 --> 31:57.040
I have a PhD.

31:57.040 --> 31:58.500
Yeah, the U.S. government,
they call me.
Oh.

31:58.500 --> 31:59.880
And they ask me about things.

31:59.880 --> 32:01.580
Congratulations.
You're still nuts.

32:01.580 --> 32:04.120
I'm not the one who's passing
out prostitute flyers.

32:04.120 --> 32:07.120
I'm -- I'm taking initiative,
okay?
No. No, Kevin.

32:07.120 --> 32:08.750
You're making a joke
out of this

32:08.750 --> 32:10.250
like you do
everything else in your life.

32:10.250 --> 32:11.420
I'm not --

32:11.420 --> 32:13.290
Mnh!

32:13.290 --> 32:14.670
[ Grunting ]

32:14.670 --> 32:15.750
What?

32:15.750 --> 32:17.540
What?
[ Exhales sharply ]

32:17.540 --> 32:19.580
Aah! Oh!
Oh, my God!

32:19.580 --> 32:20.960
Oh, my God, Kevin.
I'm so sorry.

32:20.960 --> 32:22.580
We have to get you
to a hospital.

32:22.580 --> 32:23.960
Oh, my God.
Kevin, are you okay?

32:23.960 --> 32:25.540
Go ahead.

32:25.540 --> 32:28.580
Ignore that.
[ Grunts ]

32:33.380 --> 32:35.960
You're lucky it's bruised
and not broken.

32:35.960 --> 32:37.080
Cool.

32:37.080 --> 32:38.710
That should do it.

32:38.710 --> 32:40.120
Ice it.
Keep it elevated.

32:40.120 --> 32:42.330
They'll be here
to discharge you shortly.

32:42.330 --> 32:43.420
Thank you, Doctor.

32:43.420 --> 32:45.330
Woman:
I.V. check needed in 304.

32:45.330 --> 32:47.750
Again, I am so, so sorry.
Check needed in 304.

32:47.750 --> 32:48.960
Oh, it was --
it was an accident. I --

32:48.960 --> 32:50.920
No.
[ Sighs ]

32:50.920 --> 32:53.290
Kevin, that was
a really stupid fight.

32:53.290 --> 32:55.170
No, you're --
you're right.

32:55.170 --> 32:57.710
I shouldn't be
sharing your business.

32:57.710 --> 33:00.790
It's not that.
[ Exhales sharply ]

33:00.790 --> 33:02.500
[ Sighs ]

33:04.290 --> 33:07.080
Sometimes, I, um...
[ Chuckles ]

33:07.080 --> 33:10.210
I talk to the truck,
and I pretend it's Jon.

33:10.210 --> 33:14.500
♪♪

33:14.500 --> 33:18.670
Like the -- Like the truck
is haunted by Jon?

33:18.670 --> 33:20.670
No, it's not
haunted by Jon.

33:20.670 --> 33:22.040
Because that would be amazing,
right?
Shh. Just shut up.

33:22.040 --> 33:24.080
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

33:24.080 --> 33:27.620
We bought it a few years ago,
and we worked on it together.

33:28.960 --> 33:31.580
So after the accident --
I don't know.

33:31.580 --> 33:32.710
It was just like...

33:34.330 --> 33:36.790
[ Voice breaking ] It was just
like my little conduit to him.

33:36.790 --> 33:38.330
[ Scoffs ]

33:38.330 --> 33:40.830
[ Sighs ]

33:40.830 --> 33:43.620
So if the truck gets fixed,
then no more...Jon. Okay.
I know. It's stupid.

33:43.620 --> 33:44.830
No, it's not.

33:44.830 --> 33:47.880
[ Sighs ]
It's not. I...

33:47.880 --> 33:49.620
[ Sighs ]

33:49.620 --> 33:54.290
I know I wasn't around after
Jon died, um, or before.

33:54.290 --> 33:56.080
It's okay.
It...

33:56.080 --> 33:57.670
It's really not.

33:57.670 --> 34:01.620
♪♪

34:01.620 --> 34:03.960
But I...

34:03.960 --> 34:07.250
I want to be a part
of your life now.

34:07.250 --> 34:09.500
So, let's...

34:09.500 --> 34:12.080
Let's talk to
each other...

34:12.080 --> 34:14.670
about anything, okay?

34:14.670 --> 34:17.620
-Okay.
-All right.

34:17.620 --> 34:18.710
[ Sighs ]

34:20.710 --> 34:23.460
And I can be
your haunted truck, Amy.

34:25.670 --> 34:27.830
God, you are so weird.
What?

34:27.830 --> 34:29.330
I'm gonna go
pull the car around.

34:29.330 --> 34:30.420
I'll meet you out front.

34:30.420 --> 34:32.460
[ Chuckles ] Great.

34:32.460 --> 34:35.960
[ Inhales sharply ]

34:35.960 --> 34:38.960
Got a delivery
for a Karl Gilmore

34:38.960 --> 34:40.500
from Three Roads Brewery?

34:40.500 --> 34:42.380
It's room 545.

34:42.380 --> 34:44.670
Let me call in
upstairs first.

34:44.670 --> 34:46.210
[ Sighs ]

34:46.210 --> 34:51.170
♪♪

34:51.170 --> 34:54.500
Uh, Mr. Gilmore?

34:54.500 --> 34:55.920
Hi. Kevin Finn.

34:55.920 --> 34:57.710
You called the cops
on me yesterday.

34:57.710 --> 34:59.540
Okay.

34:59.540 --> 35:01.460
[ Clears throat ]
Um, look.

35:01.460 --> 35:03.710
I was the one who convinced Jake
to talk to you,

35:03.710 --> 35:08.420
and I just want to say that
I'm -- I'm -- I'm really sorry.

35:08.420 --> 35:10.040
You're apologizing?

35:10.040 --> 35:14.210
I know
it's not enough. Um...

35:14.210 --> 35:15.880
You know, the doctor
came in here

35:15.880 --> 35:17.040
and said it wasn't
a heart attack,

35:17.040 --> 35:19.460
more like
an early warning.

35:19.460 --> 35:21.670
So I should be
kind of thanking you.

35:21.670 --> 35:24.750
In a way, you --
you saved my life.

35:26.250 --> 35:30.920
Wait. Was I supposed to be
helping you and not...

35:30.920 --> 35:32.500
not Jake?

35:32.500 --> 35:34.330
[ Gasps ]

35:34.330 --> 35:36.170
You know, you're a weird kind
of guy -- you know that?

35:36.170 --> 35:37.170
[ Laughs ]
Uh, oh.

35:37.170 --> 35:38.830
Uh...sorry.

35:38.830 --> 35:41.420
[ Chuckles ] And --
And, yes, true.

35:41.420 --> 35:43.000
It was kind of funny,
you know?

35:43.000 --> 35:46.000
He chose you to pour
his heart out to.

35:48.540 --> 35:50.330
You're a stranger.

35:50.330 --> 35:51.380
He couldn't hurt
my feelings.

35:51.380 --> 35:53.170
[ Chuckles ]

35:53.170 --> 35:55.960
He was really afraid to --
to hurt you.

35:55.960 --> 35:58.880
At the end of the day,
his happiness

35:58.880 --> 36:00.210
is the most
important thing,

36:00.210 --> 36:02.210
and it's a lot
more important

36:02.210 --> 36:04.670
than any of that
tradition crap.

36:04.670 --> 36:06.830
That's great.
[ Chuckles ]

36:06.830 --> 36:09.460
And Anheuser-Busch
is after me

36:09.460 --> 36:10.580
to give me
a boatload of money

36:10.580 --> 36:12.250
for my whole outfit.

36:12.250 --> 36:13.580
Also great.

36:13.580 --> 36:15.420
[ Laughs ]

36:15.420 --> 36:20.120
Well...um, get well soon,
Mr. Gilmore.

36:20.120 --> 36:21.500
[ Chuckles ]

36:23.710 --> 36:26.710
[ Indistinct conversations ]

36:26.710 --> 36:31.380
♪♪

36:31.380 --> 36:32.790
[ Breathes deeply ]

36:32.790 --> 36:34.500
♪♪

36:34.500 --> 36:36.290
[ Elevator doors close,
machinery whirring ]

36:36.290 --> 36:38.040
♪♪

36:41.580 --> 36:44.500
[ Ominous music plays ]

36:44.500 --> 36:54.210
♪♪

36:54.210 --> 36:58.460
♪♪

36:58.460 --> 37:01.120
[ Gasping ]

37:01.120 --> 37:05.920
♪♪

37:05.920 --> 37:08.460
Help!

37:08.460 --> 37:09.830
[ Man shouting
in native language ]

37:10.960 --> 37:11.880
[ Gasps ]

37:13.170 --> 37:14.750
[ Elevator bell dings ]

37:14.750 --> 37:16.170
[ Spits ]

37:18.920 --> 37:20.420
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

37:20.420 --> 37:23.580
Man: Case manager, please report
to Physical Therapy.

37:23.580 --> 37:25.330
Case manager
to Physical Therapy.

37:25.330 --> 37:32.500
♪♪

37:32.500 --> 37:41.460
♪♪

37:41.460 --> 37:43.080
Why are you wet?

37:43.080 --> 37:44.830
[ Siren wailing ]

37:44.830 --> 37:47.420
I was swimming.

37:49.830 --> 37:53.580
What drugs
did they give you?

37:53.580 --> 37:58.000
I was in the elevator,
and then, I was in water.

37:58.000 --> 38:00.460
It looked like some other
country. Someone was yelling.

38:00.460 --> 38:02.210
A vision.

38:02.210 --> 38:03.620
A vision!

38:03.620 --> 38:05.040
You accomplished
your mission,

38:05.040 --> 38:07.830
and the Universe
has rewarded you.

38:07.830 --> 38:09.250
But it didn't
make any sense.

38:09.250 --> 38:10.790
I-It's a piece
of the puzzle.

38:10.790 --> 38:12.460
The more you build
your spiritual power,

38:12.460 --> 38:14.880
the more you'll see.

38:14.880 --> 38:16.960
Another step towards finding
one of the righteous.

38:16.960 --> 38:18.540
Ugh.

38:18.540 --> 38:20.040
This is a lot. Is --

38:20.040 --> 38:22.790
Are you sure that I'm --
I'm the one to save us?

38:22.790 --> 38:24.500
You're not gonna have to
do this alone.

38:24.500 --> 38:26.380
Okay.

38:26.380 --> 38:28.830
Before I existed --

38:28.830 --> 38:32.210
before anything existed --
there was nothing.

38:32.210 --> 38:34.420
I was nothing.

38:34.420 --> 38:36.750
Total emptiness.

38:36.750 --> 38:39.790
I'm not going back to that.

38:39.790 --> 38:43.170
I think I understand
what you're saying.

38:43.170 --> 38:45.790
You want to be
my partner in crime...
Ugh.

38:45.790 --> 38:47.420
-My ride or die...
-Mnh-mnh.

38:47.420 --> 38:49.380
My friend and my lover.

38:49.380 --> 38:51.460
Sorry.
I was just saying things,

38:51.460 --> 38:53.170
and that -- that last one
just came out.

38:53.170 --> 38:54.920
Sorry.

38:54.920 --> 38:56.000
[ Semisonic's "Closing Time"
plays ]

38:56.000 --> 38:57.290
♪ Closing time ♪

38:57.290 --> 38:58.960
Hey. That's so weird.

38:58.960 --> 39:02.580
I was just listening
to this song at Kristin's.

39:02.580 --> 39:06.420
The Universe is always
telling you something.

39:06.420 --> 39:08.500
♪ Closing time ♪

39:08.500 --> 39:09.830
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

39:09.830 --> 39:11.380
♪ Turn all of the lights on ♪

39:11.380 --> 39:13.120
♪ Over every boy
and every girl ♪

39:13.120 --> 39:14.420
[ Clears throat ]

39:14.420 --> 39:16.120
Hello.

39:16.120 --> 39:17.960
Kevin: Hey, babe.
Sorry I haven't called.

39:17.960 --> 39:20.080
I've been so busy.

39:20.080 --> 39:21.380
Kevin?

39:21.380 --> 39:24.250
Yeah. Got this
sociology midterm.

39:24.250 --> 39:26.420
[ Scoffs ]

39:26.420 --> 39:28.210
Wait, are you drunk?

39:28.210 --> 39:31.920
No, but my roommate,
uh, is pledging Beta,

39:31.920 --> 39:33.620
and he had to shotgun
like 10 beers,

39:33.620 --> 39:36.120
so that's pretty dope.

39:36.120 --> 39:37.880
Um...

39:37.880 --> 39:40.880
Anyway, I-I-I got
your message yesterday.

39:40.880 --> 39:43.460
♪ I know who I
want to take me home ♪

39:43.460 --> 39:44.750
Yesterday?

39:44.750 --> 39:47.540
Yeah.
And, um...

39:47.540 --> 39:49.330
I owe it to you
to say that

39:49.330 --> 39:51.250
I feel like doing
a long-distance relationship

39:51.250 --> 39:52.620
is not working.

39:52.620 --> 39:55.040
♪ Take me home ♪

39:55.040 --> 39:56.330
I see.

39:56.330 --> 39:58.880
Yeah, but, um...

39:58.880 --> 40:01.920
But I'll never forget
about you...

40:01.920 --> 40:05.120
um...ever.

40:05.120 --> 40:07.920
Like, I bet
every other girl I date,

40:07.920 --> 40:11.120
even in my 20s and 30s,

40:11.120 --> 40:15.330
I will still always
compare them to you.

40:15.330 --> 40:16.960
♪♪

40:16.960 --> 40:19.790
But...anyway,

40:19.790 --> 40:23.290
I think we should, uh --
we should probably break up.

40:23.290 --> 40:25.460
Yeah. Yeah.

40:25.460 --> 40:26.830
Probably.

40:26.830 --> 40:28.620
Cool, cool.

40:28.620 --> 40:31.620
Uh, well, look, um, you probably
want to hang up on me,

40:31.620 --> 40:35.210
um, just for
the closure part.

40:35.210 --> 40:38.080
♪ Closing time ♪

40:38.080 --> 40:40.290
[ Laughs ]

40:40.290 --> 40:43.120
♪ Every new beginning comes from
some other beginning's end ♪

40:43.120 --> 40:44.210
[ Vehicle approaches ]

40:44.210 --> 40:46.620
Amy: Kevin!

40:46.620 --> 40:48.000
Kevin!

40:48.000 --> 40:50.210
[ Music ends ]

40:50.210 --> 40:54.460
♪♪

40:54.460 --> 40:57.250
Hey!
[ Laughs ]

40:57.250 --> 40:59.620
[ Engine starts ]

40:59.620 --> 41:01.000
Want a ride?

41:01.000 --> 41:02.710
[ Chuckling ]
Oho, you know I do.

41:02.710 --> 41:07.040
♪♪

41:07.040 --> 41:09.540
Oh!
This is great.

41:09.540 --> 41:11.330
Yeah.
It came out okay.

41:11.330 --> 41:13.170
And now I have a car.

41:13.170 --> 41:14.500
No, you don't
have a car.

41:14.500 --> 41:16.540
-Why not?
-You'll ruin it!

41:16.540 --> 41:18.120
-I will not.
-What happened to your last car?

41:18.120 --> 41:20.420
That's...

41:20.420 --> 41:22.710
I mean, yeah,
that's a fair point. Yeah.

41:22.710 --> 41:24.540
[ Chuckles ]
Reese!

41:24.540 --> 41:26.460
Come for a ride with us.

41:26.460 --> 41:30.040
I'm good.
You guys go without me.

41:30.040 --> 41:32.080
-All right.
-Okay.

41:32.080 --> 41:34.290
[ Gearshift clicks ]

41:34.290 --> 41:35.790
Whoo-hoo!

41:35.790 --> 41:40.290
♪♪

41:40.290 --> 41:42.420
Ooh, hey, let's ask the haunted
truck if I should have him.

41:42.420 --> 41:43.420
-Shut up.
-Shh!

41:43.420 --> 41:44.620
What's that,
haunted truck?

41:44.620 --> 41:45.580
"Kevin should drive me"?
Did you hear it?

41:50.330 --> 42:00.250
♪♪

42:00.250 --> 42:10.290
♪♪

42:10.290 --> 42:18.830
♪♪
